# Project Rules

This repository contains a static personal academic website generated by
`build.py`.

## Build Workflow

- Run `python build.py` after editing site data or generator code.
- The build reads `publication_list.bib` and `talk_list.bib`, then regenerates
  `index.html`, `publications.html`, and `talks.html`.
- Python build dependencies are listed in `requirements.txt`.

## Editing Guidance

- Prefer editing the source data files and `build.py` instead of manually
  editing generated HTML pages.
- Update `get_personal_data()` in `build.py` for profile, bio, social links,
  and footer changes.
- Update `authors.json` when adding a linked author who is not already present.
- Update `assets/site.css` for visual styling changes.
- Add publication thumbnails under `assets/img/publications/`.
- Add talk thumbnails under `assets/img/talks/`.
- Add PDFs, posters, and slides under `assets/pdf/`.

## Content Fields

Publications in `publication_list.bib` use standard BibTeX fields such as
`title`, `author`, `booktitle`, and `year`, plus optional custom fields:
`img`, `html`, `pdf`, `code`, `video`, `supp`, `poster`, `highlight`,
`award`, and `equal_contribution`.

Talks in `talk_list.bib` use `title`, `booktitle`, `year`, `img`, `slides`,
`video`, and optional `highlight`.

## Display Behavior

- Entries with `highlight = {true}` appear on the homepage.
- Highlighted publications receive a light amber background on the full
  publications page.
- Publication `award` text is displayed after the title.
- `equal_contribution = {N}` marks the first N publication authors with
  asterisks.
